        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-09-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Adams</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 97.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 25, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of September 6, No. 38, has been
                    received.</p>
                <p>Our naval force is rapidly increasing, and the command of it has recently been
                    reorganized. We are preparing for some vigorous demonstrations on the coast, to
                    begin in about ten days; and I trust, therefore, that we shall be able to defeat
                    on this side the enterprises of the insurgents which we have been unable to
                    prevent on the other.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
